Description: This DH5α strain is grown and harvested from a vial of Library Efficiency® DH5α™ Competent Cells (Catalog No.: 18258012, Invitrogen). It is harvested at an OD550 of 0.535, and made competent by a 10-min incubation with FB medium on ice. The cells were immediately freezed with LN2.
1.Cloning experiments using limiting amounts of DNA
2.Blue/white screening on X-Gal or Bluo-Gal (φ80dlacZ∆M15 marker)
4.Hosting of M13mp cloning vectors using a lawn of DH5α-FT TM, DH5αF' TM, DH5αF'IQ TM, JM101, or JM107 for plaque formation.
2.Sensitivity to Antibiotics: Unknown, supposedly sensitive to all antibiotics
1. Thaw the cells on ice until last ice crystal dissappear.
2. Add 5uL of 2ng/μL(or as required) pUC19 to cells.
5. Chill the cells on ice for 1min30sec.
6. Add 200μL of S.O.C. to the cells.
8. Take 30μL and plate out the cells to an ampcillin-LB plate.
9. Take 270μL and plate out the cells to an ampcillin-LB plate.
